The paper presents a deep neural network approach for automatic seizure detection using EEG data. This involves capturing spectral, temporal, and spatial information, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the focus on EEG data and seizure detection suggests relevance to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
